    "body": "Issue can be reproduced if turn on Developer option \"Do not keep activities\" in Android and put app on the background and than back. After this open Wallet and grey screen is shown. In addition, Maker Market starts to show \"Not connected\":\r\n![do not keep activities](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/26102003/8bec8fec-3a33-11e7-8f39-4faa9972dd9e.png)\r\n![not connected maker market](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/26102004/8bedfc92-3a33-11e7-810f-4825928ee232.png)\r\n![grey wallet](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/26102005/8bf05974-3a33-11e7-9011-93ef02cb0c71.png)\r\n\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7SlFlUkQtc0NtbFU\r\nLog: \r\n[20171605115827-logcat.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/1004019/20171605115827-logcat.txt)\r\n\r\nSteps: \r\n- enable option \"Do not keep activities\"\r\n- run Status\r\n- open Wallet (see it opens fine)\r\n- open Maker Market (see it opens fine)\r\n- switch to some other app, so Status is on background\r\n- switch back to Status\r\n- open Wallet - it shows grey screen\r\n- open Maker Market - it shows \"Not connected to Ethereum\"\r\n\r\nAbout \"Do not keep activities\" \" When this option is enabled, the Android OS will destroy an activity as soon as it is stopped. It is intended to help developers debug their apps. For example, it can simulate the case that Android will kill an activity in the background due to memory pressure\" http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22400859/dont-keep-activities-what-is-it-for\r\n\r\n### Instabug\r\nhttps://dashboard.instabug.com/applications/status-10bb8cbc-15f6-44f0-8c7a-db478dc34d7d/beta/bugs/444",
